<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9078> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9078" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "71? p. 752, footnote 386" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7043> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7043" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor 77 in Asia. In MRR 2.89, refer also to L. Robert, Monnaies antiques en Troade 16-17; C. Nicolet et al., Insula Sacra 118-119. Censor 61. A new study of the Lex Gabinia-Calpurnia de Delo of 58 (CIL 1(2).2500), by which the island was freed from tribute, yields at line 21 the following text: . . . IN LO]CATIONE Q[U]AM L(UCIUS) CAE[SAR C(AIUS) CURIO CENS(ORES) I]NSULAE DELEI FECERU[NT ... (C. Nicolet et al., Insula Sacra 149 for the text, and esp. 84-96, and 111-125 for the discussion). The locatio in question would most naturally be the one made by the most recent censors, i.e., those of 61, who have remained unknown (see MRR 2.179). The editors have shown that the L. CAE(sar) in this inscription should be the consul of 64, and make it also probable that a long-known inscription of Ilium honoring a L. Iulius Caesar, a censor (OGIS 440-ILS 8770; cf. P. Frisch, Die Inschriften von Ilion 172), which has been referred to his father (142). Cos. 90 (see MRR 2.32-33), should in fact be referred to him.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6296> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6296" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Sacerd., CIL 12.1, p. 60, no. 3-ILS 9338, no. 3; of. Grueber, CRRBM 2.501. Lucius Caesar's name is not preserved on the inscription, but it is probable that he is the one whom Sempronius succeeded (see Münzer, Hermes 52 [1917] 152-155). On Sempronius, see PIR 3.194, no. 260; De Laet no. 332." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6091> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6091" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These five consulars, selected from all factions, were, appointed early in March to serve on a second embassy to Antony, but upon reconsideration Servilius and Cicero withdrew and the embassy was not sent (Cic. Phil. 12, passim, esp. 1-2 and 18, with the names, and 28; Dio 46.32.2-4; see D.-G. 1.201-205; H. Frisch, Cicero's Fight for the Republic 239-247)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5777> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5777" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In an unprecedented procedure, Antony, the Master of Horse, named Lucius Caesar Praefectus Urbi when he left the city to deal with mutinous troops in Campania (Dio 42.30.1-2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5585> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5585" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate of Caesar in 49 (Caes. BC 1.8.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5475> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5475" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate under Caesar in Gaul (see 52, and 49, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5412> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5412" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate under Caesar in Gaul (see 52, and 49, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5359> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5359" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate of Caesar in Gaul, in charge of the Narbonese province (Caes. BG 7.65.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4884> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4884" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed by the Praetor under an antique procedure to try Rabirius for perduellio (Dio 37.27; see Tribunes of the Plebs, on Labienus)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4809> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4809" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 12.2.906, 962; Cic. Att. 1.2.1; Sull. 56; Pis. 8; Sall. Cat. 17.1; Ascon. 82 C; Dio 37, Index, and 6.4, and 10.1; Chr. 354 (Caesare et Turmo); Fast. Hyd. (Lucio Caesare et Figulo), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. See Degrassi 131, 490f. Under these Consuls decrees of the Senate were passed limiting the attendants upon candidates for election, and making the collegia illegal (Cic. Mur. 71; Pis. 8, and Ascon. 8 C)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4678> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4678" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "2 The latest date possible under the Cornelian law." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4634> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4634" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Inaugurated Lentulus as Flamen Martialis (Macrob. Sat. 3.13.11; cf. Fest. 154 L; Priscian 8. 15; Macrob. Sat. 1. 16.29)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4310> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4310" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served in Asia (OGIS 444-SEG 4.664). See Magie, Roman Rule in Asia Minor 2.1119, note 24." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/9920> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #9920" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
	dprr:isAboutPerson <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Person/2044> ;
